.TH "intel_engine_context_size" 9 "intel_engine_context_size" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
intel_engine_context_size \- return the size of the context for an engine
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u32" intel_engine_context_size
.BI "(struct intel_gt *gt "  ","
.BI "u8 class "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "gt" 12
the gt
.IP "class" 12
engine class
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Each engine class may require a different amount of space for a context
image.
.SH "RETURN"
size (in bytes) of an engine class specific context image
.SH "NOTE"
this size includes the HWSP, which is part of the context image
in LRC mode, but does not include the "shared data page" used with
GuC submission. The caller should account for this if using the GuC.
